Description:
Walk to shops from attractive unit
If you're looking for a homely unit to live in or invest, this 2-bedroom unit is sure to entice. Set in a quiet, secure block of units in Whittington, the lovely residence is just a short walk to the shopping precinct of Bellarine Highway. The home offers privacy, restful living areas and low maintenance surrounds ensuring an easy lifestyle.
The spacious living room features ceiling fans, gas heating and air conditioning, and a well-equipped kitchen caters adequately for those who enjoy cooking with ample bench space and cupboards. Built-in robes and ceiling fans are offered in the bedrooms and the laundry and bathroom are combined for ease of use. An enclosed outdoor area serves as a handy spot for quiet time or casual dining with visitors.
The comfortable, appealing unit is neat and tidy at every turn and is currently leased at $215 per week. A shed and single garage complete the home. Simply move in today and relish the good life.

Description:
VENDOR WANTS IT SOLD!
Here's the ultimate in brick family homes, situated in the best pocket of Whittington within walking distance to transport, shops, schools and a 5 minute drive from the CBD.
This family home has been well loved and meticulously cared for and presented by the owner and is sure to tick boxes for the owner occupier or investor alike.
The home offers a massive formal lounge and dining with ducted heating & huge sun drenched windows to allow the winter warmth, and then opens out to the kitchen which is the heart of the home. Overlooking the rear gardens the kitchen is warm and light filled and has a breakfast bar, dining and family room and leads out to the rear veranda.
All 3 bedrooms are generously sized with BIR, the master has ENS, and the fourth single bedroom would be suitable for an office or study.
If you're looking for car space we have a double garage, and a single enclosed carport with rear garden shed and lush low maintenance gardens wrapping around the property. With an approx. rental return of: $330-$350 pw. Additional features: gas ducted heating, ceiling fans in main living, central bathroom, spacious kitchen, fully fenced front and rear yards.

Description:
Easy To Live In, Easy To Let Out
Located within 10 minutes from Geelong CBD and close to local schools, shops and public transport this property is sure to impress first home buyers, tradesmen and investors.
Comprising of formal lounge room including original art deco mantel piece, reverse cycle air conditioning, wood heater & polished timber floors, the updated kitchen includes dishwasher, breakfast bar and new flooring which compliments a separate meals area. There are 4 bedrooms including the master with built in robes, bathroom with separate shower and vanity with modern semi recessed basin.
The side drive has lock up gates and leads to a large concreted area and huge shed which can fit 4 cars (approx. 12 x 6) plus extra undercover storage space at the rear of the shed.
The home has been re roofed, re stumped and has low maintenance gardens, On an allotment of 796m2 ( approx ) the long term potential of the property could be to subdivide the block and build a second dwelling out the back. (STCA)
Inspect today and you are sure to be impressed by the quality of the home and shedding /storage, perfect for extra cars/trailers etc.

Your Fabulous Hidden Oasis Awaits In Great Area
Looking for your affordable dream home then this one is a big surprise. Comprising of 3 massive separate living areas including a massive rumpus room, a formal lounge room, as well as a large dining, spacious kitchen and meals area this one's got space for the biggest of families and entertainers.
With a master bedroom at one end of the home comprising of full ensuite and walk in robe, and the other two bedrooms with BIR + study at the opposite end, this one's well thought out. Description:
A winner in Whittington - huge block!
If its room to move you're looking for, you're guaranteed to find all the space you need at this outstanding home in Whittington. In a quiet neighbourhood close to conveniences, the modern 3BR residence sits on a massive 855sqm block that backs onto the peaceful setting of the Bellarine Rail Trail. The tall leafy trees of the trail create a lovely aspect from the home's extensive outdoor timber decking that is an impressive spot to host visitors over a bbq or party. The home is fitted with an intercom, security system, ceiling fans and air conditioning to ensure the entire house is comfortable and welcoming all year round. The living areas and functional kitchen are refreshingly light and bright, and from the dining table you can see straight outside to the undercover alfresco.
There are 3 large bedrooms featuring BIRs and WIR in the main plus a large bathroom and laundry. There is plenty of room for the growing family at this house, especially if children want to play outside. A block of this size would not be complete without shedding and car space - and this home certainly doesn't disappoint with 4-car garage, double carport, driveway and workshop. Enjoy this fantastic well-presented family home today.

Description:
Two bedroom cottage home with a modern touch.
Living in a small flat and wanting more room? Property prices to high for you to buy? This may be the break you have been looking for. Priced to sell and in a great central location.
This home is located close to schools, sporting facilities, public transport and only 10 minutes by car from CBD of Geelong. This property will surely appeal to many first home buyers, the renovator within and or the astute investor. The small cottage home has plenty of charm with its original high ceilings, faux fire place mantle in the master and polished floor boards in the bedrooms and kitchen area. As you enter in the home you pass the bedrooms on the left and right and then the hallway opens up to a large lounge area. From the lounge you have direct access to the kitchen, bathroom or the rear courtyard via two large wooden doors.
The home has had a modern update while keeping with cottage feel of the home. The bathroom has been updated to include a large shower, toilet, vanity unit and tiled floor. Making good use of the space available the laundry has also been installed in the bathroom, keeping the main wet areas together. The kitchen has been updated with laminate bench tops, s/s upright gas cook top and oven and ample storage and bench space. The home is temperature controlled by a reverse cycle air conditioner placed in the lounge.
The block has been subdivided into two separate titles with common ground allocated for both properties to use once 2nd dwelling has been constructed. The north facing courtyard at the rear of the property is ideal for entertaining and has room allocated for a single car garage to be built.

Description:
Move Straight In!
Newly renovated, this rendered BV home is situated in a quiet court and is sure to suit a first home buyer, family or investor, with a potential rental income of $300/week.
Comprising formal lounge with easy care floating floorboards and a reverse cycle airconditioner, opened to the brand new kitchen with stainless steel appliances and dishwasher adjoining the dining area, three bedrooms all with built in robes, renovated bathroom with separate bath and shower, new vanity and separate toilet. Newly painted in tasteful, neutral tones throughout.
Outdoors is a large undercover pergola, plenty of enclosed lawn for children to play, carport, and 6 x 9 m steel shed with major bench and electricity. Allotment approximately 697 sqm. Just move in and enjoy all the hard work the present owners have done.
